{
  "texts": [
    "Therefore, in this study, a CAD system called \"Color-CADx\" is designed to accurately classify various subclasses of colorectal cancer (CRC).",
    "Color-CADx employs three convolutional neural network (CNN) models with distinct architectures, as opposed to using a single model.",
    "It additionally combines the deep features of these CNNs.The classification process does not solely rely on the spatial information provided by images but also utilizes spectral demonstration.",
    "Thus, it utilizes the discrete cosine transform (DCT) with zigzag scanning to merge the deep features from the three CNNs and achieve a spatial-spectral representation.",
    "The DCT is employed to decrease the vast dimensions of the combined features."
  ]
}